    "OMP_NUM_THREADS=9 #Still shows error below regarding the optimal usage of threads. My laptop has 16 threads:(8-core Xeon)\n",
    "\n",
    "wcss=[] # Define list\n",
    "for i in range(1,32):  #tries 1 to 32 clusters\n",
    "    kmeans = KMeans(i)\n",
    "    kmeans.fit(X)\n",
    "    wcss_iter = kmeans.inertia_\n",
    "    wcss.append(wcss_iter)\n",
    "\n",
    "number_clusters = range(1,32) # creates the graph below for identifying a 'knee' to discern the optimal # of clusters\n",
    "plt.plot(number_clusters,wcss)\n",
    "plt.title('The Elbow title')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Number of clusters')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('WCSS')"
   ]
  },

    "Conclusion: k-means cluster is a powerful tool to identify similar groups in an unsupervised learning algorithm.\n",
    "Adding the power of finding the most orthogonal variables or 'features' shows how one may go about the next steps in teasing apart meaningful variables and to which classes certain data point likely 'belong' to and how we defing which ones are 'close' to each other."
